should focus on what the error handler returns rather than how the trace system processes it—that points toward unit testing, though I could note integration as a secondary consideration.\n\nNow I'm weighing the test levels more carefully. The valid markdown JSON parsing is solidly unit territory, but the trace record behavior sits somewhere between unit and integration depending on whether the trace sink is a separate component being tested or just part of the error handler's output. I'm leaning toward integration for that one since the trace sink seems to be a distinct piece of the system. For the remaining behaviors, the error policy function is unit, real process execution is system, the full hook invocation is system-level E2E, and distinguishing between malformed JSON and valid markdown is unit.\n\nLooking at confidence levels across these: valid markdown parsing is very likely unit, while the trace record behavior is more split between unit and integration, with integration slightly favored.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10599,"cache_read_input_tokens":3097,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10599},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3244ca79-1c74-403e-bda9-a84565aca38b","uuid":"5908f9d3-2743-4658-b5a1-f2fe3029b490"}
